NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The general rule is, the double relieves responder of having to bid even with 6 or 7 points. So responder should only bid if they have something useful to say. For example, if they have a 5 card suit or a good 4 card suit they should bid. Or they can bid 1NT which shows something slightly stronger than the normal 6-10 1N would say had Babs passed.|
PG| ***** 20 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|As Gail, I would have bid 1N with her hand to show that I am not completely broke--having 8-10. If we change the hand around, such that one of the kings was in the club suit, e.g you have K Q 8 7 5 of clubs you might bid 2@C. The auction 1@H-dbl-2@C denies 10 points. Many less experience people don't know that. You always redouble with 10 points, so any bid other than redouble (or 2N which is Jordan and shows a limit raise) denies 10 points.|
