^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|1NT is the bid that most would make with Kia's hand including me. But Marty Bergen would argue his hand is too strong for 1N opener. His Bergen Starting Points are 17 plus 1 length plus 1 quality suit plus 1 adjust 3 v(4 aces/10 and only 1 quack) for a total of 20. So Bergen would argue his hand is closer to a 2N bid than a 1N bid, but would probably say it is acceptable to open 1@D intending to jump to 2N.|
