NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|In general I use straight HCP to decide how much my hand is worth in NT. But I also count my Starting Points, and if they are off by 2 or more then I adjust. For example, on this hand, because I have 3 more starting points than HCP, I would consider it worth a 1@D opener followed by a 2N (18-19) rebid.|
PG| ***** 55 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|I count my Bergen Starting Points. If my starting point count comes to 19 or more, I then consider the hand too strong to open 1N--I am 2 points more than an opening 1N bid. Similarly, it is possible that I have a very quacky hand with 15 HCP but that only counts to 13 Starting Points. In that case, I would consider the hand too weak to open 1N.|
